{
  "stem": "19969.6",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 88.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we had a chance to meet with German officials and with the American embassy in Bonn, Germany and-- and then go on to Munich and go through the museum at Dachau.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "A very rewarding visit, I think.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We learned a lot about the problems that the Germans are having today.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they're having a neo-Nazi movement.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We have the same thing here in the United States.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "What caught our attention was that in Holocaust memorial services that we have every year, we were going to have people picket with signs saying this is all a hoax, the Holocaust was a hoax.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then more disturbing to me was a few years ago-- --about two years ago, I was speaking in San Diego as a guest of a Marine base at Camp Pendleton, California, and one of the people in the audience, since the public was invited, one of the people in the audience came up to me and showed me a leaflet, I have copies of it here, which anyway was put out by an outfit called-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] --the Historical Institute of Costa Mesa, California.",
      "word_count": 87
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they put out a pamphlet which says-- has a bunch of questions and answers, which in effect states that the Holocaust never happened.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "An in that literature, it says that no Jews were killed in concentration camps, that was all made up and that the crematoriums in the concentration camps that still exist over there were constructed after the war as tourist attractions.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Well, you have to be sick, very sick, to go out and preach today that the Holocaust never happened.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And these are people with great hatreds.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Obviously, they are a neo-Nazi type or Hitler worshippers.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
